worldwide; however, the findings of studies in Japan are inconsistent. Recently, the smoking rate has gradually decreased
We performed a meta-analysis of smoking status in a large Japanese cohort of (1) 1845 schizophrenia patients and
196 845 general population and (2) 842 schizophrenia patients and 766 psychiatrically healthy controls from 12 studies over a
